preview_comments.text: 2, 3, 1 for me. Never played the Arabian nights levels in Crash 3 so they’re kinda lost on me...plus I don’t love that aesthetic. It’s a biiiiig gap between Prehistoric Playground (B-tier track) and Spyro Circuit (F-tier track). I need Nina’s place to be top notch

caption.text:
Favourite Grand Prix track from the first three 🏆? For me it’s a really close tie between Twilight Tour and Prehistoric Playground but I prefer Twlight Tour as it feels real smooth to drive on plus the aesthetic and visual design is really good

Spyro Circuit is in last place for me. Beenox did a really good job with the visuals and aesthetics (I like how there’s gems and baskets instead), but it feels really cramped to drive on plus you’re just going straight most of the time

What’s your rankings mine are
1. Twilight Tour
2. Prehistoric Playground
3. Spyro Circuit

Can’t wait for Nina’s Nightride, I have a feeling that’s gonna be on the same quality as the first two

So happy Dragon Quest XI is finally out on the Switch! 👏🏽⚔️
*•*•*•*•*
It might be a while before I get to it tho, I still need to beat Octopath Traveler, and I hate starting a new RPG before finishing the last cuz then it’ll probably stay on my backlog forever 😭 Just like DQVII, which has a 100+ hour main story and which I probably need to restart cuz I forgot where I’m at 😩 #gamerproblems 😂
*•*•*•*•*
Anyway, what is y’all’s favorite Dragon Quest game? Mine is for sure DQV ❤️❤️ I wish more ppl have played it because it seriously has one of the best RPG stories I’ve ever played. It follows a boy into adulthood, and you eventually get to be in a party with your wife and kids (you can even choose who you marry which affects dialogue and improves replayability), which is just so freakin’ cute.. I 100/10 recommend 👍🏽
*•*•*•*•*

caption.text: لعبتنا اليوم هي (سيبادر مان) اي بالمعنى الرجل العنكبوت قد نزلت لعبة في آواخر سنة ٢٠١٨ حصرايا على جهاز بلاي استيشن ٤ وقد ترشحت من افضل العاب مغامرة بنفس السنة. قصة لعبة تبدا عندما تسقط اكبر منظمين جرام في مدينة ويقول سوفة تدمر مدينة بسببك ومن هناك تحدث كثير من الامور في مدينة وظهور كثير من مجرمين لم تكن تعرفهم ولا اريد اتكلم عن القصة امثر لانها فعلا قوية ومن نفس كتاب قصص مافل . نظام العبة قد ابدعوا المطورين وقدموا لنا فعلا لعبة سيبادر مان من ناحية قفز من بناية الى اخرى ومن سلسل الى مخبأ الأعداء وحتى أيضا اسلوب القتال فعلا ممتعة وفي كثير من الامور لم استطع اغطيها في تقرير ولكن في خلاصة الأمر أستطيع القول هو لعبة فعلا لا تتطوف بصراحة وانصح فيها بشدة عيبها الوحيد هو حصريا على بلاي استيشن فقط و تستغرق لإنهائها تقريبا ٣٠ ساعة اقيمها ٩/١٠

caption.text:
My first impressions of the N-Switch game controller from Ipega are surprisingly positive. I was interested in it because it was a mix of third party joycons, which I mainly wanted for better chances with the controls sticks, and a Switch grip that would not only make handheld mode more comfortable but also offer more support to the connection points on the side when holding it.
.
I played Yooka-Laylee for a few hours with it tonight and despite it not having a full back like I thought it did, it still is surprisingly supportive yet lightweight. The layout is a tad awkward but I adjusted to it fine and the feel is decent. The buttons definitely feel strange and the d-pad is a little stiff, but the sticks are actually pretty nice, especially with those concave tops to keep your thumbs in place.
.
A few things to note are that there's no NFC compatibility, no rumble, no motion controls, and to get this working you have to first turn wired pro controller connection on in the setting with a different controller, THEN slide the Switch into place, and don't try updating the controller or it will go out of sync after failing. So it basically just feeds off the battery of the Switch for power, but it didn't seem to hog much power compared to playing with other controllers as far as I've noticed.
.
You'll see the Wii U gamepad here not only for a size comparison but also a reminder. The Switch can be used not just as a console, a handheld, or a portable console via tabletop mode. It can also be used for off TV play! It's a pretty limited concept, sure, but if you just want to watch something on your TV while you play then it's great to have around the house. It's not going to be a great travel companion due to its size and awkward shape, and while on the TV you might as well use a pro controller, but just playing off your TV at home... this thing is pretty nice.
.
One word of warning: Your Switch might be a little tough to get out of this thing. That's nice to know it won't come falling out, even if you tip it upside down, but it can be a little scary prying it out of there. I'm hoping worst case scenario will be that the accessory breaks.
.
Thoughts on this... thing?

title: God Bless Pseudo Saturn

caption.text:
A few years ago I became obsessed with experiencing the Sega Saturn library for the first time, but was immediately disheartened when I realized how much money I’d need to spend to do so. Luckily, I figured out how to flash Pseudo Saturn to an Action Replay cart and burn any Saturn game I felt like playing. It’s a wonderful thing . 👍

caption.text: Finally copped Pokken. Time to train. #pokken #pokkentournament #pokkentournamentdx #nintendo #nintendoswitch

Well kinda annoyed 😞 so I purchased a switch lite to use exclusively portably obviously. Having the same Nintendo account tethered between a switch lite & switch ver. 2 is simple & sharing save data is somewhat simple but unfortunately play time doesn’t register properly 😕 example my play time for link’s awakening says “10 hours or more” which is incorrect because I know it’s over 20 hour because I have the parental control app & it monitors play time. Hopefully Nintendo fixes this 😤

Ni no Kuni: Wrath of the White Witch

It is a role-playing video game, developed by Level-5. It was released for the PlayStation 3 in Japan in November 2011, and published in Western regions by Namco Bandai Games in January 2013. caption.text:
Post-op day 6: It's been a few days since my last post, and I'm already feeling dramatically better. Liquids are going down easier, and now that the gas pain is gone it's easier to listen to cues from my body. I feel like I have to relearn my body's "hungry" and "full" feelings, which is a trip. Did anyone else experience this? I feel like they're slightly different sensations than they were before surgery. 
I'm still dealing with a bit of pain on my right side, and I'm thinking it might be in the muscle? It's still hard to bend over, sit up, sneeze, cough, etc. (Omg, sneezing sends me through the ROOF 😭😵). I'm just managing it with tylenol now, and I'm walking an average of 2-4 miles per day. My current daily average for liquid intake is: 
Protein shakes: 16-20 oz 
Water: 40-50 oz 
Other: 4-8 oz 
Aside from the pain my spirits are high, and I've been more than content resting at home and happily spending time with my #nintendoswitch 🎮 and my furbabies. 🐶🐱

« Nintendo Umumkan Brain Age / Brain Training untuk Nintendo Switch »

Melalui akun Youtube Nintendo Japan, Nintendo mengumumkan game Dr. Kawashima Brain Age / Brain Training untuk Nintendo Switch.

Game ini sempat populer di Nintendo DS, yang mana juga menjadikan Nintendo DS menarik perhatian bagi non-gamer sekalian.

Dr. Kawashima Brain Age / Brain Training saat ini baru diumumkan untuk region Jepang, belum ada kabar mengenai tanggal rilis versi globalnya.

Di kesempatan yang sama, Nintendo juga mengumumkan perangkat stylus resmi Nintendo Switch.
